Suggestions:
1. `inputLabelHint` might be an inaccurate name. It is not a hint about the input label - it is a hint about the param itself, so it is equivalent to `placeholder`, hence maybe just `hint`. Not very familiar with the feature so please use your judgment.
2. The condition `if (['clientId', 'clientSecret'].includes(parameterName))` in `inputLabelDisplayName` for `credText` allows for Client ID and Client Secret to be translated once and reused across all OAuth creds params. It does not seem that hints will benefit from this - and even if they will, certainly not from Client ID and Client Secret.
3. In the comment `Display hint for a top-level param.`, I would remove `Display` as it is implied. `Display` exists in the docstring for `displayName` because it is part of the property name.
4. In the comment `Hint (hint text) for an input, whether top-level or nested.`, I would remove `(hint text)` as it does not add anything. `(tooltip text)` exists in `inputLabelDescription` because it clarifies where the description is shown, so there it is helpful.

